r!.id, 'folder', folder.id, 'editor')) {\n      res.status(403).json({ error: 'Insufficient permissions' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const { name, parentId } = req.body;\n\n    if (name !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof name !== 'string' || !name) {\n        res.status(400).json({ error: 'Folder name must be a non-empty string' });\n        return;\n      }\n      folder.name = name;\n    }\n\n    if (parentId !== undefined) {\n      if (parentId !== null) {\n        const parent = store.folders.get(parentId);\n        if (!parent) {\n          res.status(404).json({ error: 'Parent folder not found' });\n          return;\n        }\n        // Prevent circular reference (walk up ancestor chain)\n        if (wouldCreateCycle(store, folder.id, parentId)) {\n          res.status(400).json({ error: 'Cannot move folder: would create a circular reference' });\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n      folder.parentId = parentId;\n    }\n\n    res.json(folder);\n  });\n\n  // Delete folder\n  router.delete('/folders/:id', requireAuth, (req: AuthRequest, res) => {\n    const folder = store.folders.get(req.params.id);\n    if (!folder) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Folder not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (!hasPermission(store, req.user!.id, 'folder', folder.id, 'owner')) {\n      res.status(403).json({ error: 'Insufficient permissions' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Delete all documents in the folder\n    for (const [docId, doc] of store.documents.entries()) {\n      if (doc.folderId === folder.id) {\n        store.documents.delete(docId);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Delete subfolders recursively\n    deleteFolderRecursive(store, folder.id);\n\n    store.folders.delete(folder.id);\n\n    // Remove shares for this folder\n    store.shares = store.shares.filter(\n      (s) => !(s.resourceType === 'folder' && s.resourceId === folder.id)\n    );\n\n    res.status(204).send();\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n\nfunction wouldCreateCycle(store: Store, folderId: string, proposedParentId: string): boolean {\n  let current: string | null = proposedParentId;\n  while (current) {\n    if (current === folderId) return true;\n    const folder = store.folders.get(current);\n    current = folder ? folder.parentId : null;\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction deleteFolderRecursive(store: Store, folderId: string) {\n  const subfolders = Array.from(store.folders.values()).filter(\n    (f) => f.parentId === folderId\n  );\n\n  for (const subfolder of subfolders) {\n    // Delete documents in subfolder\n    for (const [docId, doc] of store.documents.entries()) {\n      if (doc.folderId === subfolder.id) {\n        store.documents.delete(docId);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Recursively delete subfolders\n    deleteFolderRecursive(store, subfolder.id);\n\n    store.folders.delete(subfolder.id);\n\n    // Remove shares\n    store.shares = store.shares.filter(\n      (s) => !(s.resourceType === 'folder' && s.resourceId === subfolder.id)\n    );\n  }\n}\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":122,"oldLines":10,"newStart":122,"newLines":13,"lines":["       return;","     }"," ","-    // Delete all documents in the folder","+    // Delete all documents in the folder and their shares","     for (const [docId, doc] of store.documents.entries()) {","       if (doc.folderId === folder.id) {","         store.documents.delete(docId);","+        store.shares = store.shares.filter(","+          (s) => !(s.resourceType === 'document' && s.resourceId === docId)","+        );","       }","     }"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
